## Mission
YouTube growth app: channel/competitor analysis, idea generation, thumbnail generation, and anything that measurably improves creator growth (CTR, retention, upload consistency).

---

## Tech & Platform
- Runtime: **bun** (not npm/yarn).
- Framework: **Next.js App Router** (`app/`).
- **No Next.js middleware** ÔÇö use **proxy.ts** for request proxying.
- Payments: **Stripe**. Webhook routes are externally-invoked entrypoints ÔÇö never assume unused.

---

## Architecture & Layers

Canonical architecture: `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md`. Imports flow **downward only**.

```
app/ (entrypoints)
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ components/, lib/api/, lib/features/, lib/adapters/, lib/server/
components/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ lib/features/, lib/shared/
lib/features/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ lib/ports/, lib/shared/
lib/adapters/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ lib/ports/, lib/shared/
lib/server/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ lib/features/, lib/adapters/, lib/shared/
lib/api/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ lib/shared/
lib/ports/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ (nothing ÔÇö pure types)
lib/shared/
  ÔööÔöÇÔöÇÔľ║ (nothing ÔÇö leaf layer)
```

### Forbidden imports
- `lib/features/` must NOT import from `lib/adapters/`, `components/`, or `app/`.
- `lib/adapters/` must NOT import from `lib/features/`, `components/`, or `app/`.
- `lib/ports/` must NOT import from `lib/features/`, `lib/adapters/`, or `components/`.
- `lib/shared/` must NOT import from `lib/features/`, `lib/adapters/`, or `components/`.
- `components/ui/` must NOT import from `lib/adapters/` or `app/`.

If a change requires a forbidden import, the code is in the wrong layer. Move it.

### Layer responsibilities

**`app/`** ÔÇö entrypoints only (routes, pages, layouts). Must remain thin.
- `app/api/**/route.ts`: orchestrate only ÔÇö middleware Ôćĺ use-case Ôćĺ response. No business logic, no direct DB/LLM/API calls.
- `app/**/page.tsx`: fetch via `lib/server/`, pass props to components, define metadata.
- `app/sitemap.ts` and `app/robots.ts` exist; sitemap omissions Ôëá dead routes.

**`components/`** ÔÇö UI layer:
- `ui/` ÔÇö presentational primitives (no business logic)
- `layout/` ÔÇö app shell, headers, sidebars
- `features/<domain>/` ÔÇö feature-specific client components + hooks

**`lib/features/<domain>/`** ÔÇö domain logic. Each domain owns:
- `types.ts`, `schemas.ts`, `errors.ts` (extending `DomainError`), `use-cases/`, `index.ts`
- Features receive validated inputs, return domain types or throw `DomainError`. No `Response` objects.
- Access external I/O through port interfaces only.

**`lib/adapters/<provider>/`** ÔÇö I/O only: HTTP calls, SDK wrappers, caching, retries, data mapping.
- Must NOT make business decisions or import feature code.

**`lib/ports/`** ÔÇö pure type contracts for external I/O.

**`lib/shared/`** ÔÇö cross-domain utilities. Must be used by 3+ domains. When in doubt, keep in the feature.

**`scripts/`** ÔÇö CLI/maintenance scripts. **`tests/`** ÔÇö unit/integration tests. **`proxy.ts`** ÔÇö request proxying.

