## File Structure (MANDATORY)
- **One component per file.** Extract sub-components to their own files.
- **Hooks in separate files.** Custom hooks (`use*.ts`) get dedicated files.
- **Pure logic in separate files.** Utilities/transformers/computation Ôćĺ own `.ts` file.
- **Shared types** used by 2+ files Ôćĺ `*-types.ts`.
- **Target: <150 lines per file.** Refactor immediately if exceeded.

---

## Naming Conventions

| Item | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Folders/files | kebab-case | `competitor-search/` |
| React components | PascalCase.tsx | `ExampleWidget.tsx` |
| Types/interfaces | PascalCase | `CompetitorVideo` |
| Functions | camelCase | `discoverCompetitors` |
| Zod schemas | PascalCase + `Schema` | `DiscoverQuerySchema` |
| Error classes | PascalCase + `Error` | `CompetitorNotFoundError` |
| Use-case files | camelCase verb phrase | `discoverCompetitors.ts` |
| CSS modules | `style.module.css` or `<Component>.module.css` | |

Before creating a new utility, search: `lib/shared/` Ôćĺ `lib/features/` Ôćĺ `lib/adapters/`. Extend existing functions.

---

## Barrel Files
- `index.ts` = re-export only. No logic, no side effects.
- Never import your own barrel (no circular `import from './index'`).

---

## Error Handling & Validation
- Domain errors extend `DomainError` from `lib/shared/errors.ts`. Each feature has `errors.ts`.
- Route handlers use `withErrorHandling`; `toApiError()` maps `DomainError` Ôćĺ `ApiError`.
- Common codes: `NOT_FOUND`, `UNAUTHORIZED`, `FORBIDDEN`, `LIMIT_REACHED`, `INVALID_INPUT`, `EXTERNAL_FAILURE`, `TIMEOUT`, `RATE_LIMITED`.
- Zod schemas in `lib/features/<domain>/schemas.ts`. Route handlers validate with `withValidation()`.
- Use-cases receive validated types ÔÇö no re-parsing. Infer: `type Input = z.infer<typeof InputSchema>`.
- Use guard clauses / early returns. Handle edge cases explicitly. Never log secrets.

---

## Rendering & State
- Default to **React Server Components** and server-side data fetching.
- Minimize `'use client'`, `useEffect`, `useState`. Use client components only for interactive state, browser APIs, realtime UX.
- Server-only modules use `import "server-only"`.
- Client state: **Zustand** (global UI), **TanStack React Query** (fetching/caching).

---

## Adding a New API Route

```ts
import { createApiRoute } from "@/lib/api/route";
import { withAuth } from "@/lib/api/withAuth";
import { withValidation } from "@/lib/api/withValidation";
import { jsonOk } from "@/lib/api/response";
import { SomeBodySchema } from "@/lib/features/<domain>";
import { doSomething } from "@/lib/features/<domain>";

export const POST = createApiRoute(
  { route: "/api/path/here" },
  withAuth({ mode: "required" },
    withValidation({ body: SomeBodySchema }, async (_req, _ctx, api, { body }) => {
      const result = await doSomething({ userId: api.userId!, ...body });
      return jsonOk(result, { requestId: api.requestId });
    })
  )
);
```

